Class Union3<A,B,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.types.Union2<A,B>
      • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.types.Union3<A,B,C>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataType<Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Union4

    @InterfaceAudience.Public
public abstract class Union3<A,B,C>
extends Union2<A,B>
    The Union family of DataTypes encode one of a fixed collection of Objects. They provide convenience methods which handle type casting on your behalf.
    See Also:
    Union2

        public boolean isNullable()
